and have them run the DNA from
Daniel's case through CODIS,

12:33.237 --> 12:34.357
see if they come up with anything.

12:34.405 --> 12:36.269
The federal database?
That's a long shot.

12:36.326 --> 12:38.449
People like this usually
don't end up in CODIS.

12:38.614 --> 12:40.129
These jerkwads might.

12:40.219 --> 12:43.011
They doth protest too much,
especially that Eddie DuBar guy.

12:44.488 --> 12:46.308
If it may please the court,
Madeline Scott,

12:46.345 --> 12:47.357
- for the petitioner.
- THOMPSON: Ms. Scott,

12:47.394 --> 12:49.207
I've heard every 14th
Amendment argument

12:49.244 --> 12:51.119
on the books today, denied them all.

12:51.156 --> 12:52.746
Do you have anything new
to add to the mix?

12:52.816 --> 12:54.988
Davon Watkins's position is unique:

12:55.113 --> 12:58.504
he isn't seeking a stay of
execution, he already has one.

12:58.564 --> 13:00.653
We're simply asking
that the court uphold it.

13:00.690 --> 13:03.662
Officer Sampson was
killed by Omar Blackwell.

13:03.699 --> 13:07.098
He was ordered to do so by Troy
Dalton, a known drug dealer.

13:07.135 --> 13:08.455
We have this affidavit that clearly...

13:08.491 --> 13:09.895
I'm familiar with the facts,

13:09.932 --> 13:12.240
and your stay was
conditioned upon the finding

13:12.277 --> 13:14.535
of new evidence in support
of your client's innocence.

13:14.572 --> 13:16.980
- Your Honor, moving forward...
- There is no new evidence here.

13:17.098 --> 13:18.264
Petition denied.

13:18.301 --> 13:19.690
[GAVEL BANGS]

13:19.980 --> 13:21.283
[SIGHS]

13:22.207 --> 13:23.528
THOMPSON: <i>Next on the docket,</i>

13:23.565 --> 13:24.823
<i>State v. Alexander Corwin.</i>

13:26.418 --> 13:27.740
<i>This matter from Cuyahoga County...</i>

13:27.777 --> 13:29.434
- I'm not giving up.
- Neither am I.

13:29.471 --> 13:31.411
- What's next?
- We take down Troy D.

13:31.448 --> 13:32.709
There's no breaking down that door.

13:32.746 --> 13:34.168
Then we break down a different door.

13:34.229 --> 13:35.645
Meaning?

13:35.682 --> 13:37.403
Troy D ordered the hit on Sampson

13:37.440 --> 13:38.576
because his cover was blown.

13:38.613 --> 13:40.043
That's the only way
this all makes sense.

13:40.080 --> 13:42.334
Well, then the question is how
it was blown and who blew it?

13:42.371 --> 13:43.514
His handlers would know.

13:43.551 --> 13:46.190
The police aren't exactly
forthcoming with information.

13:46.273 --> 13:48.348
We make a Freedom
of Information Act request.

13:48.442 --> 13:50.367
- Better make it fast.
- I'll file the motion right away.

13:55.236 --> 13:56.464
I got something.

13:56.501 --> 13:57.902
- Hmm.
- As you predicted,

13:57.939 --> 14:00.397
O Wise One, CODIS came up with bupkis

14:00.434 --> 14:02.326
on the DNA from Janet Dale's rape kit.

14:02.420 --> 14:03.652
But...

14:04.525 --> 14:06.236
our rapist/murderer has a son,

14:06.486 --> 14:08.946
and he wants to know a little
bit more about his ancestry.

14:09.189 --> 14:11.443
You submitted DNA
to a private genetics company?

14:13.021 --> 14:14.352
Can I use this?

14:14.413 --> 14:16.638
Familyrootsfinder.com.

14:17.907 --> 14:19.268
Fred Jenks.

14:19.439 --> 14:21.363
Our bad boy had a son
who's looking for his father.

14:21.400 --> 14:22.568
That's genius.

14:22.605 --> 14:25.243
Now, if he's already found
his dad, we're halfway home.

14:25.478 --> 14:26.952
EASY: Yeah.

14:27.085 --> 14:28.543
All right.

14:30.345 --> 14:31.938
WOMAN: <i>Fred's still at work.</i>

14:32.048 --> 14:33.892
I'm his mother, Karina Jenks.

14:33.974 --> 14:35.783
Please, have a seat.

14:36.205 --> 14:37.505
Thank you.

14:39.462 --> 14:41.159
Your son submitted his DNA

14:41.196 --> 14:43.337
to the familial finder websites.

14:43.400 --> 14:45.642
We'd actually like
to talk to his father.

14:45.736 --> 14:47.689
Uh, so would Fred.

14:47.726 --> 14:49.566
I'm sure that's why he used that site.

14:49.603 --> 14:52.967
- Fred doesn't know his father.
- Right, but you do.

14:53.550 --> 14:56.548
I haven't seen him in decades.
What's this all about?

14:56.640 --> 14:58.338
EASY: There's no easy way to say this.

14:58.407 --> 15:01.432
DNA matching your son's
biological father

15:01.707 --> 15:03.460
has been linked to a crime.

15:03.602 --> 15:05.769
BODIE: It's, uh, more likely than not

15:05.806 --> 15:09.150
he raped and murdered
a sorority girl 25 years ago.

15:10.947 --> 15:12.279
Janet Dale?

15:13.759 --> 15:14.844
You knew her?

15:14.915 --> 15:17.493
I was her Theta Omega sister
for about a year,

15:17.530 --> 15:19.497
but they convicted somebody.

15:19.587 --> 15:21.650
Our client, but he didn't do it.

15:21.821 --> 15:24.814
No DNA match, no other evidence
to support his conviction.

15:24.950 --> 15:27.220
I'm sorry, but Fred's father...

15:27.359 --> 15:28.955
is Janet Dale's murderer.

15:32.566 --> 15:35.826
Fred's been asking about him
since he was a little boy.

15:40.135 --> 15:41.831
Uh...

15:42.621 --> 15:45.925
I was a sophomore at Sheridan.

15:47.680 --> 15:50.003
The Phi Kapps were having a...

15:50.097 --> 15:53.419
"pimps and hos" party.

15:53.634 --> 15:55.421
I drank too much.

15:56.103 --> 15:59.087
I went to his room to sleep it off.

16:01.770 --> 16:03.972
I woke up not being able to breathe.

16:04.542 --> 16:06.917
Someone's hands were around my throat.

16:07.904 --> 16:10.582
Then I felt someone on top of me.

16:13.225 --> 16:15.392
Inside me.

16:17.304 --> 16:19.896
I always thought I would fight back...

16:21.285 --> 16:23.285
...but I was paralyzed.

16:25.484 --> 16:27.402
He was going to kill me,

16:27.478 --> 16:29.828
and I was letting him.

16:32.872 --> 16:34.386
I'm so sorry.

16:34.753 --> 16:36.737
None of this is your fault.

16:37.740 --> 16:39.815
I know that now.

16:39.909 --> 16:41.558
But back then, I...

16:42.394 --> 16:46.316
Every time I saw him on campus,
I got sick to my stomach.

16:47.011 --> 16:49.642
And when I learned
I was pregnant, I just ran.

16:49.966 --> 16:51.966
I quit school.

16:54.253 --> 16:58.074
[LAUGHS]: That's probably
more than you were asking for.

16:58.262 --> 16:59.678
That's okay.

17:03.082 --> 17:05.991
Who, uh... who did it?

17:06.836 --> 17:08.426
Was it Eddie DuBar?

17:08.464 --> 17:09.994
KARINA: <i>Eddie? No.</i>

17:10.261 --> 17:12.772
Eddie was actually
my boyfriend at the time.

17:13.127 --> 17:14.848
<i>He could come across as a jerk,</i>

17:14.886 --> 17:17.059
but he was always really sweet to me.

17:17.996 --> 17:21.180
The man who raped me
was his best friend,

17:21.217 --> 17:22.749
<i>Bob Callaway.</i>

17:23.566 --> 17:25.453
That's my son's father.

17:26.413 --> 17:28.078
That's your killer.

17:34.108 --> 17:35.953
FRY: Gentlemen, I thought I made myself

17:35.990 --> 17:37.574
clear in the prior hearing.

17:37.640 --> 17:39.783
This is an entirely new
legal issue, Your Honor.

17:40.085 --> 17:41.946
I need a court order
to get a DNA sample

17:41.983 --> 17:43.257
from Robert J. Callaway.

17:43.294 --> 17:44.368
Who?

17:44.405 --> 17:46.275
The former Illinois Bar
Association president,

17:46.312 --> 17:47.853
Your Honor, Bob Callaway.

17:47.890 --> 17:50.251
Oh, Bob Callaway, nice man.

17:50.288 --> 17:51.905
We've had dinner on occasion.

17:52.147 --> 17:53.630
So what is this all about?

17:53.772 --> 17:56.726
DNA, Judge. We want to test it.

17:57.147 --> 17:59.116
Absolutely not.

17:59.319 --> 18:01.213
The rape charge has been dismissed.

18:01.350 --> 18:03.446
The DNA of person or persons unknown

18:03.483 --> 18:05.306
has no bearing
on the murder conviction.

18:05.343 --> 18:07.755
EASY: Your Honor, that ruling
flies in the face of reason.

18:07.792 --> 18:09.801
Excuse me?

18:12.163 --> 18:13.946
I'm sorry if I offended
Your Honor in any way

18:13.983 --> 18:15.125
during these proceedings,

18:15.163 --> 18:16.643
but my client shouldn't
bear the brunt of...

18:16.679 --> 18:18.321
Oh, you haven't offended me.

18:18.438 --> 18:21.429
You haven't even appeared before
me in some time, Ezekiel.

18:21.562 --> 18:23.344
But it is good to see you again.

18:23.504 --> 18:25.346
[GALLERY MURMURING]

18:28.932 --> 18:30.374
Your Honor?

18:31.294 --> 18:32.985
Motion denied.

18:39.327 --> 18:43.093
Yeah, they keep saying just
"take it one day at a time,"

18:43.185 --> 18:45.357
but, uh... [SIGHS]

18:45.593 --> 18:47.593
it's more like every second

18:47.670 --> 18:50.241
of every single day.

18:50.327 --> 18:53.457
I know. It's the same for me.

18:55.561 --> 18:57.035
How come you called me?

18:57.072 --> 18:58.771
I saw you at Toby's funeral.

18:58.832 --> 19:00.439
So did your sister.

19:00.520 --> 19:02.326
I already told her
I didn't know anything.

19:02.488 --> 19:05.011
She said that-that you almost
OD'd, and I just thought,

19:05.048 --> 19:06.295
you know, I thought maybe we could...

19:06.413 --> 19:07.629
What?

19:08.076 --> 19:10.010
Compare battle scars?

19:11.510 --> 19:12.932
[SIGHS]

19:15.636 --> 19:17.878
LEVI: When I was in prison, I, um,

19:17.993 --> 19:22.682
I got protection from the guys
that were running heroin.

19:22.779 --> 19:25.223
You keep away from it the best you can.

19:25.633 --> 19:27.223
Things started to spiral.

19:27.301 --> 19:30.636
And if it wasn't for Madeline
and my folks, I'd be dead.

19:30.987 --> 19:33.247
Three years in N.A. taught me that

19:33.313 --> 19:35.489
all of our stories have
different beginnings,

19:36.511 --> 19:38.068
but similar endings.

19:38.379 --> 19:39.812
So how'd you start?

19:39.901 --> 19:42.503
- [CHUCKLES]
- I-I heard some rumor about

19:42.540 --> 19:45.026
girls who were doing
Adderall in high school.

19:45.075 --> 19:47.653
We were just trying to stay skinny.

19:47.870 --> 19:49.763
[CHUCKLES]: What? Why?

19:52.901 --> 19:54.147
Hey.

19:54.214 --> 19:57.138
I just want to know what
happened to Rosemary, okay?

19:57.807 --> 20:01.164
You know, I-I just found out
she was doing Adderall.

20:01.201 --> 20:04.143
I-I didn't know if you guys
were even friends, but I...

20:05.595 --> 20:07.820
Heather Dupinski,
she connected all of us.

20:08.245 --> 20:11.245
It was something really special
when we first started hanging.

20:11.643 --> 20:14.100
- Then what happened?
- Rosemary died.

20:16.050 --> 20:17.979
Nothing was the same after that.

20:18.259 --> 20:19.619
Do you think
that any of those other girls

20:19.655 --> 20:21.288
could've killed Rosemary?

20:21.417 --> 20:23.120
Like Heather Dupinski?

20:24.728 --> 20:26.561
It's not impossible.

20:26.737 --> 20:28.792
But, I mean,
there were other girls, too.

20:28.831 --> 20:32.956
Look, we were stupid teenagers,
but we felt like a family.

20:33.125 --> 20:36.198
Okay, when Rosemary died,
it changed all of us.

20:38.917 --> 20:40.066
All right, a few

20:40.103 --> 20:41.831
conservative-leaning constituents

20:41.868 --> 20:44.231
feel that Rosemary's Law
doesn't push hard enough.

20:44.268 --> 20:46.044
They want a death penalty rider.

20:46.081 --> 20:49.036
If you go pro-death penalty,
you can kiss the Chicago vote

20:49.073 --> 20:50.278
and the election goodbye.

20:50.315 --> 20:52.286
The rider may cause a bit
of a hit in the major cities,

20:52.323 --> 20:54.753
but it will be offset
by an uptick in the suburbs.

20:55.050 --> 20:57.864
Mr. Zahn says, and I agree,
that with the press you'll get

20:57.901 --> 20:59.786
for passing the law, it's a net win.

20:59.823 --> 21:01.833
CONNOR: Not if you're
seen as compromising

21:01.870 --> 21:03.753
personal values for political gain.

21:03.868 --> 21:05.393
Are you compromising?

21:05.690 --> 21:06.990
Where do you stand?

21:07.149 --> 21:09.399
Are you pro-death penalty or not?

21:13.448 --> 21:16.091
When you've seen the things I've seen,

21:16.451 --> 21:18.052
the cases I've tried...

21:20.120 --> 21:22.839
...it's almost impossible
not to be pro death penalty.

21:23.245 --> 21:24.714
I've spent a good
deal of my life trying

21:24.751 --> 21:26.180
to seek justice against

21:26.220 --> 21:27.714
the worst of humanity,

21:27.823 --> 21:29.604
and I have never sought
the death penalty

21:30.502 --> 21:32.664
unless I was truly convinced
it was called for.

21:33.134 --> 21:34.520
NOAH: So then, what's the problem?

21:34.557 --> 21:36.536
The problem is
he'd be taking a position

21:36.573 --> 21:39.355
on a controversial issue
when he doesn't need to.

21:39.375 --> 21:41.015
NOAH: Yeah, well,
there's a time to play politics

21:41.051 --> 21:42.842
and a-a time to man up.

21:45.768 --> 21:47.197
I'll take it under advisement.

21:47.278 --> 21:48.677
Thank you, sir.

21:55.682 --> 21:58.617
Uh, moldy trail mix
or expired mystery bar?

21:58.676 --> 22:00.432
I'm good with coffee.

22:00.902 --> 22:03.305
Come over here. You got to see this.

22:04.026 --> 22:05.497
We got our FOIA response,

22:05.534 --> 22:08.708
and apparently, at the time
of Officer Sampson's murder,

22:08.745 --> 22:10.318
the East Cleveland PD was involved

22:10.355 --> 22:12.464
in a joint task force with
the Drug Enforcement Agency.

22:12.565 --> 22:14.386
The Feds? Okay.

22:14.423 --> 22:16.888
Uh, do we know who
Officer Sampson's handler was?

22:16.925 --> 22:19.137
- Who put him in the park that night?
- No, it doesn't say.

22:19.174 --> 22:21.241
But I did find this interesting.

22:22.465 --> 22:24.966
That's Troy D. So?

22:25.151 --> 22:27.312
You see that guy standing behind Troy?

22:27.619 --> 22:30.143
His name is Tyler Lauten.

22:30.190 --> 22:32.940
He's Troy's head of security
and personal bodyguard.

22:32.977 --> 22:34.458
Want to know what job
he had before he started

22:34.494 --> 22:35.730
working for Troy?

22:35.932 --> 22:38.784
He was a DEA agent in Cleveland.

22:39.034 --> 22:40.492
- You're kidding.
- Nope.

22:40.581 --> 22:42.364
And guess who was the head
of the joint task force

22:42.401 --> 22:43.829
with the East Cleveland PD?

22:43.893 --> 22:45.061
- Tyler Lauten.
- Mm-hmm.

22:45.098 --> 22:46.832
Well, he was Sampson's boss
back in the day.

22:46.893 --> 22:48.267
He set him up.

22:49.369 --> 22:50.551
[EXHALES]

22:50.667 --> 22:52.943
Violet, I think you found our guy.

23:00.088 --> 23:02.255
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

23:02.557 --> 23:04.909
- Here he is.
- TYLER: Ladies.

23:05.136 --> 23:06.677
Tyler Lauten, head of security.

23:06.714 --> 23:07.786
How may I help you?

23:07.823 --> 23:10.440
We have some questions
for you about Steve Sampson.

23:10.536 --> 23:12.019
[CLEARS THROAT]

23:15.557 --> 23:17.573
MADELINE: So we know
that you were a DEA agent

23:17.640 --> 23:19.531
and that you put
Steve Sampson in City Park

23:19.568 --> 23:21.159
the night that he was killed.

23:21.255 --> 23:22.633
Now you work for Troy D.

23:22.670 --> 23:24.011
You see how that looks.

23:24.110 --> 23:25.312
Actually, I don't.

23:25.761 --> 23:27.559
You got your facts backwards.

23:27.667 --> 23:29.651
Officer Sampson was on the job.

23:29.800 --> 23:30.997
He called me

23:31.034 --> 23:33.066
and told me he was heading to the park,

23:33.103 --> 23:34.495
to meet a C.I.

23:35.003 --> 23:36.298
The shooting was random.

23:36.421 --> 23:38.904
Your current boss
ordered the hit on Sampson.

23:39.518 --> 23:40.661
And you put him there.

23:40.698 --> 23:42.404
No, I didn't.

23:42.753 --> 23:45.099
And my current employment by Mr. Dalton

23:45.136 --> 23:47.044
is perfectly legit.

23:47.534 --> 23:49.677
Hell, half of Cleveland
law enforcement works for him.

23:49.753 --> 23:53.231
Also, Troy had no reason
to kill Officer Sampson.

23:53.362 --> 23:54.955
Investigation was going nowhere.

23:54.992 --> 23:57.104
We were ready to close up shop.

23:57.201 --> 24:00.565
What happened with Sampson
was... bad luck.

24:00.697 --> 24:02.364
Davon Watkins is gonna die

24:02.401 --> 24:04.076
in four days for a
crime he didn't commit.

24:04.182 --> 24:07.634
You used to be a DEA agent,
you were one of the good guys.

24:08.182 --> 24:09.895
What the hell happened to you?

24:11.464 --> 24:13.489
- Mr. Dalton.
- Tyler.

24:14.405 --> 24:16.071
So who do we have here?

24:16.253 --> 24:19.184
I'm Madeline Scott,
this is Violet Price.

24:19.221 --> 24:20.831
We represent Davon Watkins.

24:20.917 --> 24:23.925
Right. That poor kid
that's on death row.

24:23.996 --> 24:26.214
Personally, I'm not a big fan
of the death penalty.

24:26.448 --> 24:29.261
It affects our people in
a grossly disproportionate way.

24:29.300 --> 24:33.003
We spoke to Omar Blackwell
before he was killed in prison.

24:33.237 --> 24:34.364
He told us what you did.

24:34.401 --> 24:37.533
Omar was a desperate man looking
to make peace with his son.

24:37.846 --> 24:39.611
You and I both know he wasn't reliable.

24:39.729 --> 24:41.871
Then why did you kill him
for being a snitch?

24:42.721 --> 24:44.901
I think you watch
too many gangster movies.

24:45.042 --> 24:46.451
I assure you,

24:46.534 --> 24:48.845
you won't discover
anything about Officer Sampson's

24:48.882 --> 24:50.595
unfortunate death here.

24:51.768 --> 24:53.112
Isn't that right, Tyler?

24:53.245 --> 24:54.854
TYLER: That's just what I told them.

24:54.893 --> 24:56.987
- Bad luck.
- Well,

24:57.086 --> 25:00.026
I'm sorry you ladies wasted your time.

25:04.823 --> 25:06.890
MADELINE: "Bad luck." Yeah, right.

25:07.011 --> 25:08.478
[PHONE RINGS]

25:09.268 --> 25:10.839
- Sorry.
- Mm-hmm.

25:11.034 --> 25:12.338
Hello?

25:12.537 --> 25:13.989
Yes, yes. I'll accept.

25:14.026 --> 25:15.497
I just... I need a second.

25:15.893 --> 25:17.239
I just found out my parole hearing's

25:17.276 --> 25:18.817
at 10:00 a.m. tomorrow.

25:18.979 --> 25:21.077
Wren, uh...

25:21.200 --> 25:23.409
I'm in Ohio on a case.

25:23.620 --> 25:25.248
<i>My client's on death row and I...</i>

25:25.309 --> 25:26.690
You can't make it.

25:26.823 --> 25:28.843
I'm so sorry.

25:29.604 --> 25:31.353
Just... You're gonna do great, okay?

25:31.390 --> 25:34.386
Um... Look, just sit up straight,

25:34.503 --> 25:36.668
<i>talk clearly and smile.</i>

25:36.837 --> 25:38.690
<i>They won't be able
to resist your smile.</i>

25:38.831 --> 25:41.856
Hey, you've got three other
character witnesses, all right?

25:41.893 --> 25:44.556
And none of them have been
locked up, unlike yours truly.

25:46.113 --> 25:48.130
They don't know me like you do.

25:48.290 --> 25:49.841
Wren, I'm so sorry.

25:50.065 --> 25:51.700
<i>My client's gonna die
if I don't help him</i>

25:51.737 --> 25:54.390
<i>and I just really need</i> to be here, I...

25:55.872 --> 25:57.244
All right.

25:57.338 --> 25:58.729
Bye.

26:05.571 --> 26:08.138
- More coffee?
- Um... no.

26:13.040 --> 26:15.040
I've got nothing to say to you.

26:15.763 --> 26:18.513
- We know.
- We were hoping you'd talk to her.

26:21.846 --> 26:23.396
Karina.

26:23.460 --> 26:25.010
It's been a long time, Eddie.

26:29.873 --> 26:31.481
So you never suspected?

26:31.643 --> 26:34.432
Bob Callaway, that son of a bitch.

26:35.838 --> 26:37.654
I didn't know why you left school.

26:37.691 --> 26:39.770
You never returned my calls.

26:40.206 --> 26:43.030
- I'm so sorry.
- It wasn't your fault.

26:43.142 --> 26:44.474
Yes, it was.

26:45.134 --> 26:47.100
So... Janet Dale?

26:47.266 --> 26:48.831
Daniel Hernandez is serving

26:48.851 --> 26:51.000
a life sentence for a crime
he didn't commit.

26:51.217 --> 26:53.067
We need to know what happened.

26:54.356 --> 26:56.884
That night, I was still upset

26:56.921 --> 26:58.266
about you leaving school.

26:58.582 --> 27:02.381
Bob said a good rager
was the best way to forget.

27:03.453 --> 27:04.836
So we drank.

27:04.999 --> 27:06.199
A lot.

27:06.276 --> 27:07.868
We took Janet in the room.

27:08.301 --> 27:10.368
Bob asked her if she'd ever heard of

27:10.421 --> 27:11.991
a "devil's triangle."

27:12.100 --> 27:14.530
She slapped him, but he just laughed.

27:14.881 --> 27:17.733
She went to the door,
but Bob grabbed her.

27:19.039 --> 27:21.241
She tried to scream, but...

27:22.303 --> 27:24.276
Bob put his hand over her mouth.

27:25.038 --> 27:26.887
The music was so loud.

27:27.905 --> 27:29.429
I left.

27:30.932 --> 27:32.592
I was a coward.

27:35.303 --> 27:37.522
EASY: Your Honor,
we call Mr. Edward DuBar.

27:37.737 --> 27:40.266
- Who's this?
- Mr. DuBar was an eyewitness

27:40.303 --> 27:42.172
to the events of the day in question.

27:42.335 --> 27:44.048
How many times need I say it?

27:44.085 --> 27:45.891
This is not about rape anymore.

27:45.928 --> 27:47.723
We believe this testimony exonerates

27:47.760 --> 27:49.265
the petitioner of the charge of murder.

27:49.374 --> 27:51.943
Very good. Yes. Well,

27:52.252 --> 27:54.811
Deputy, please call the jury in.

27:55.026 --> 27:56.708
[GALLERY MURMURING]

27:59.526 --> 28:01.329
I, um... I'm constrained

28:01.366 --> 28:03.067
to remind Your Honor there is no jury.

28:03.229 --> 28:05.771
This is an evidentiary hearing,
Your Honor.

28:14.925 --> 28:16.511
EASY: Given the hour,

28:16.759 --> 28:19.527
may I suggest we adjourn
for the day, Judge?

28:21.467 --> 28:23.367
Yes, well...

28:24.696 --> 28:26.526
Okay, um...

28:26.698 --> 28:29.007
we're adjourned until
9:00 a.m. tomorrow.

28:29.157 --> 28:31.140
[GALLERY MURMURING]

28:41.112 --> 28:43.294
Remember when Hillary Clinton
would talk about

28:43.331 --> 28:45.465
the difference between
winning an election

28:45.584 --> 28:47.634
- and actually doing the job?
- BELLOWS: Yes.

28:47.980 --> 28:49.544
It's a loser's argument.

28:50.114 --> 28:51.854
If you're gonna run for office,

28:51.891 --> 28:53.365
win the damn election.

28:53.655 --> 28:55.245
Worry about the issues later.

28:55.292 --> 28:57.722
I'm tired of hiding
what I really believe.

28:58.073 --> 28:59.656
It's a mistake, Gore.

29:00.975 --> 29:03.668
But you seem to be making
a lot of them lately.

29:09.237 --> 29:10.769
Noah, Connor.

29:10.869 --> 29:12.826
May I see you in my office, please?

29:18.860 --> 29:20.209
Connor.

29:21.170 --> 29:23.154
You're fired. I'm sorry.

29:32.404 --> 29:34.246
NOAH: Well played.

29:34.720 --> 29:36.186
As always.

29:37.784 --> 29:39.427
[DOOR OPENS]

29:44.692 --> 29:46.483
MAN: Park it around back.

29:52.754 --> 29:54.195
Looking for me?

29:54.272 --> 29:56.105
Yes, I am.

29:56.199 --> 29:57.855
I want you to take a look around.

29:57.908 --> 29:59.349
See that school?

29:59.725 --> 30:01.417
That library?

30:02.770 --> 30:04.453
Who do you think got them built?

30:05.263 --> 30:07.354
And that nursing home is there

30:07.391 --> 30:10.230
because I put that there.

30:10.337 --> 30:11.401
So?

30:11.878 --> 30:13.849
You built the city's morgue, too.

30:13.972 --> 30:15.814
You know, ten years ago,
a white girl like you

30:15.851 --> 30:17.751
wouldn't be caught dead
on a street like this.

30:18.130 --> 30:19.456
You don't know me.

30:19.574 --> 30:21.191
And you don't know me.

30:21.357 --> 30:23.550
And you don't see how it all works.

30:24.174 --> 30:25.980
See, for the rest to live,

30:26.017 --> 30:27.870
there's always gonna be
acceptable losses.

30:27.907 --> 30:30.651
Your client, uh,
Davon what's-his-name...

30:30.777 --> 30:32.518
yeah, no...

30:32.613 --> 30:34.542
he's an acceptable loss.

30:34.789 --> 30:36.730
And as far as this city's concerned,

30:36.844 --> 30:38.511
I'm a necessity.

30:38.841 --> 30:40.991
I am East Cleveland.

30:41.735 --> 30:43.645
Davon Watkins is innocent.

30:44.198 --> 30:45.901
He will walk free.

30:46.025 --> 30:49.077
And the people responsible
for Officer Sampson's murder

30:49.114 --> 30:50.825
will be locked up.

30:51.588 --> 30:54.179
And East Cleveland will be just fine.

30:54.633 --> 30:56.464
You need to be careful.

30:58.442 --> 31:00.025
So do you.

31:04.724 --> 31:07.391
FRY: This is what I love most, Ezekiel.

31:07.550 --> 31:09.433
After the day's work is finished,

31:09.470 --> 31:11.284
you're left with just yourself,

31:11.321 --> 31:12.948
your thoughts...

31:13.355 --> 31:15.026
and the law.

31:15.489 --> 31:18.078
With all its purity and force.

31:18.769 --> 31:21.019
And magic. [CHUCKLES]

31:22.305 --> 31:24.519
And all it requires
is the determination

31:24.556 --> 31:26.761
and intellect to push and pull at it

31:26.798 --> 31:30.878
until you finally see,
as clearly as the dawn's light,

31:31.292 --> 31:33.028
the right thing to do.

31:33.139 --> 31:34.494
I know.

31:37.509 --> 31:38.830
And that's why this
is the hardest thing

31:38.866 --> 31:40.134
I've ever had to do.

31:40.198 --> 31:42.256
What are we talking about, Ezekiel?

31:42.352 --> 31:45.011
Sir, when I appeared before you
during yesterday's proceedings,

31:45.048 --> 31:47.124
- you...
- Did I lose my temper?

31:47.388 --> 31:48.737
Apologies.

31:48.784 --> 31:51.331
Since Margaret passed last year...

31:51.653 --> 31:53.686
I've had a short fuse.

31:54.508 --> 31:57.276
Judge, Mrs. Fry passed four years ago.

31:59.069 --> 32:00.718
I saw you at her funeral.

32:00.975 --> 32:03.142
How can it be that long?

32:10.095 --> 32:11.564
Judge...

32:14.080 --> 32:15.371
I think maybe this might be

32:15.408 --> 32:17.032
the right time for you to step down.

32:17.212 --> 32:18.878
Step down?

32:19.026 --> 32:20.437
From the bench?

32:20.992 --> 32:22.622
How dare you.

32:22.731 --> 32:24.656
Who do you think you're talking to?

32:24.948 --> 32:26.948
A man I admire...

32:30.233 --> 32:31.540
...and love.

32:31.894 --> 32:34.779
Well, I appreciate your concern,
but I'm fine.

32:36.595 --> 32:37.995
Sharp as ever.

32:38.150 --> 32:39.970
Really, I am.

32:44.573 --> 32:48.083
I know we probably shouldn't be
discussing an active case, but...

32:49.261 --> 32:50.839
I just wanted to give you a heads-up.

32:50.876 --> 32:52.097
Yes?

32:52.222 --> 32:54.425
I intend to cite <i>State v. Kafina</i>

32:54.462 --> 32:56.462
in my appeal of your DNA ruling.

32:56.664 --> 33:00.105
It's directly on point
and completely persuasive.

33:00.253 --> 33:02.956
Well, if you think it's relevant,

33:02.993 --> 33:05.802
I'll accept any brief
you want to submit.

33:06.230 --> 33:08.660
I confess, I don't remember the case

33:08.697 --> 33:10.636
off the top of my head.

33:12.126 --> 33:13.964
It's an excellent opinion.

33:15.628 --> 33:17.333
Brilliantly crafted.

33:18.542 --> 33:20.175
Cited hundreds of times,

33:20.212 --> 33:22.331
all the way up
to the U.S. Supreme Court.

33:22.368 --> 33:25.126
Sorry, it doesn't come to mind.

33:26.299 --> 33:27.740
Judge...

33:31.691 --> 33:34.417
Elijah, you wrote
that opinion yourself.

33:37.686 --> 33:39.354
I did?

33:46.179 --> 33:47.941
[SHUDDERS]

33:50.956 --> 33:53.980
You could have moved to recuse me,

33:54.327 --> 33:56.735
made a big deal of all this.

33:57.252 --> 33:59.020
But you didn't.

34:00.578 --> 34:03.212
You spared me the humiliation.

34:04.919 --> 34:07.086
You taught me the way.

34:09.503 --> 34:10.737
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

34:10.775 --> 34:13.359
I'll call the administrative
judge and arrange medical leave.

34:13.561 --> 34:15.027
No.

34:16.458 --> 34:19.110
I want to do this the right way.

34:21.339 --> 34:25.007
My health has deteriorated
in the past few weeks.

34:25.330 --> 34:27.284
I am a steward of justice.

34:27.511 --> 34:30.705
It remedies that
which is untenable and wrong.

34:31.056 --> 34:33.284
It's really a simple process.

34:33.492 --> 34:36.158
You look at the facts,
you apply the law,

34:36.195 --> 34:38.368
and you come up with an opinion.

34:39.636 --> 34:41.214
Now, it is my opinion

34:41.251 --> 34:43.690
that my time as a judge is over.

34:44.447 --> 34:46.706
I will step down from this matter,

34:46.744 --> 34:48.089
and this bench,

34:48.149 --> 34:49.847
effective immediately.

34:50.009 --> 34:53.495
I leave in my wake other stewards...

34:53.945 --> 34:57.447
sharp minds and gentle souls

34:57.554 --> 35:00.230
who will take care of justice
and protect her.

35:00.808 --> 35:03.648
This case and this defendant

35:04.214 --> 35:06.340
are in good hands.

35:07.480 --> 35:09.698
This court vacates
the sole remaining count

35:09.735 --> 35:11.019
against Mr. Hernandez

35:11.056 --> 35:13.208
and directs that the State
issue an arrest warrant

35:13.245 --> 35:15.068
for Robert J. Callaway.

35:15.348 --> 35:18.003
The State apologizes to you,
Mr. Hernandez.

35:18.119 --> 35:19.284
You're a free man.

35:19.375 --> 35:20.842
- [GAVEL BANGS]
- [SCATTERED APPLAUSE]

35:22.720 --> 35:24.052
Thank you.

35:29.257 --> 35:31.534
You're coming home. You're coming home.

35:31.707 --> 35:33.766
TYLER: <i>I can only tell you</i>
what I remember, Counselor.

35:34.523 --> 35:37.130
Officer Sampson called,
said he wanted to wrap up

35:37.167 --> 35:39.754
a detail with one of his
confidential informants.

35:39.862 --> 35:41.159
"No big thing," he said,

35:41.196 --> 35:43.235
so I gave him the go-ahead
to meet the C.I.

35:43.344 --> 35:44.683
For the record, who was the target

35:44.720 --> 35:47.196
of Officer Sampson's
undercover investigation?

35:47.286 --> 35:49.401
Troy Dalton, but that
investigation was winding down.

35:49.445 --> 35:51.875
And who is your current employer?

35:52.682 --> 35:54.210
Troy Dalton.

35:54.849 --> 35:56.821
Your Honor, I renew my motion

35:56.858 --> 35:58.917
that the stay of execution
previously in place

35:58.954 --> 36:00.362
for Davon Watkins be revived.

36:00.486 --> 36:02.669
Ms. Scott, in light
of the paucity of evidence...

36:02.706 --> 36:04.006
Paucity?

36:04.370 --> 36:07.300
An undercover officer
is killed on a fool's errand

36:07.337 --> 36:09.003
to meet person or persons unknown,

36:09.040 --> 36:11.394
and then that undercover
officer's boss goes to work

36:11.431 --> 36:13.601
for the target of said investigation?

36:13.638 --> 36:15.171
If that doesn't stink to high heaven...

36:15.208 --> 36:17.542
I'm not interested in how you
think things smell, Ms. Scott.

36:17.556 --> 36:19.980
We have a signed confession
from a known associate

36:20.017 --> 36:21.818
- of Mr. Dalton's.
- Now deceased.

36:21.855 --> 36:23.146
Executed.

36:23.183 --> 36:25.516
The same way Officer Sampson
was executed.

36:25.553 --> 36:26.863
THOMPSON: Ms.
Scott, do you have any other witnesses?

36:26.899 --> 36:28.433
- Your Honor...
- It's a yes-or-no question!

36:28.470 --> 36:30.287
No. They're all being murdered.

36:31.854 --> 36:34.801
Petitioner Davon Watkins's
final appeal is denied.

36:34.838 --> 36:37.605
His execution will
proceed as scheduled.

36:37.642 --> 36:38.964
[GAVEL BANGS]

36:42.921 --> 36:44.680
You can do it.

36:54.425 --> 36:56.097
So, I hear you're coming around to

36:56.134 --> 36:57.918
the proposed death penalty addendum

36:57.955 --> 36:59.097
to Rosemary's Law.

36:59.134 --> 37:00.526
You know, I used to think that

37:00.644 --> 37:02.825
life in prison was worse than death,

37:03.636 --> 37:05.440
'cause you had to sit there all day

37:05.534 --> 37:06.980
struggling with your guilty conscience

37:07.017 --> 37:08.097
for the rest of your life.

37:08.134 --> 37:09.688
And then I realized that

37:09.769 --> 37:11.632
most of the accused...

37:12.691 --> 37:14.089
...don't have a conscience.

37:14.126 --> 37:18.003
So, no struggle, no remorse.

37:18.055 --> 37:19.229
I think you're right.

37:19.266 --> 37:20.816
People who kill, they...

37:22.252 --> 37:23.636
...they don't feel anything.

37:23.747 --> 37:26.628
Bottom line, I need to win.

37:27.019 --> 37:28.936
But I have to do it on my own terms.

37:29.435 --> 37:31.354
I wouldn't want it any other way.

37:31.425 --> 37:32.903
Really?

37:34.393 --> 37:36.073
Because I would have thought
you would want

37:36.110 --> 37:38.363
more of a return on your five million.

37:38.727 --> 37:42.018
I want a friend in Springfield,
but other than that...

37:42.401 --> 37:43.787
[LAUGHS]

37:44.056 --> 37:46.440
Gore, you got me all wrong. Y...

37:47.866 --> 37:49.675
You have big dreams,

37:50.065 --> 37:53.097
and I'm gonna make 'em come true.

37:59.344 --> 38:00.919
The battle's not over, Davon.

38:00.956 --> 38:02.151
We still have one more day to fight.

38:02.188 --> 38:03.284
AMINA: We're gonna resist

38:03.321 --> 38:05.352
until the last possible moment.

38:06.054 --> 38:07.420
Thank you.

38:08.117 --> 38:10.977
I really appreciate
everything you've done for me.

38:11.920 --> 38:14.964
I just want you to know I'm ready.

38:15.094 --> 38:17.036
Don't say that, Davon.

38:18.803 --> 38:21.495
When they take one
of us guys to that room,

38:21.610 --> 38:24.761
all of us, we bang on our cell doors

38:24.798 --> 38:27.669
<i>and scream as loud as we can</i>

38:27.847 --> 38:30.565
<i>so that that man knows
that he's not alone</i>

38:30.687 --> 38:32.236
<i>when he leaves this earth.</i>

38:32.342 --> 38:35.835
And that sound...
it used to terrify me.

38:36.248 --> 38:37.985
<i>'Cause I thought what if I'm actually</i>

38:38.022 --> 38:39.981
<i>alone when it's my time?</i>

38:40.175 --> 38:42.056
What if nobody believes me?

38:43.676 --> 38:46.229
They've taken a guy
every day this week.

38:46.981 --> 38:48.347
But guess what.

38:48.854 --> 38:51.714
I'm not scared anymore.

38:52.402 --> 38:53.933
You know why?

38:54.404 --> 38:56.100
Because you believe me.

38:57.948 --> 39:00.557
The people, they heard the truth,

39:01.070 --> 39:02.940
and that's because of you.

39:06.223 --> 39:08.264
We're still gonna fight this.

39:14.539 --> 39:18.065
Once a death row inmate's
final appeal is denied,

39:18.222 --> 39:20.302
his death day is set.

39:21.052 --> 39:22.918
And Davon's is today.

39:23.140 --> 39:25.641
Now, only the governor
and the Supreme Court

39:25.678 --> 39:28.846
and you stand between him
and this final judgment.

39:28.996 --> 39:32.332
You can demand that
Davon Watkins be given

39:32.369 --> 39:33.693
a stay of execution

39:33.730 --> 39:37.074
because he is an innocent man.

39:40.081 --> 39:42.309
<i>"The Moving Finger writes;"</i>

39:42.438 --> 39:45.370
<i>"and, having writ, Moves on:"</i>

39:45.448 --> 39:47.901
"nor all thy Piety nor Wit"

39:47.954 --> 39:49.913
"Shall lure it back"

39:50.108 --> 39:52.126
<i>"to cancel half a Line,"</i>

39:52.456 --> 39:54.323
<i>"Nor all thy Tears"</i>

39:55.131 --> 39:57.214
<i>"wash out a Word of it."</i>

39:58.159 --> 40:00.198
<i>Do not let the last line</i>

40:00.277 --> 40:02.854
<i>on the life of Davon Watkins
be written.</i>

40:04.307 --> 40:05.698
Not yet.

40:05.725 --> 40:07.026
♪ <i>Feel like it's over now?</i> ♪

40:07.063 --> 40:08.471
[CROWD SHOUTING]

40:08.508 --> 40:10.479
VIOLET: <i>We've submitted
an emergency petition</i>

40:10.516 --> 40:12.221
<i>to the U.S. Supreme Court,</i>

40:12.262 --> 40:14.779
<i>and we've sought clemency
from the governor.</i>

40:15.714 --> 40:17.456
<i>But the hour is finally here.</i>

40:17.493 --> 40:20.195
Maketh me to lie down
in green pastures.

40:20.425 --> 40:23.201
- [LOCK CLICKS]
- [PRAYING QUIETLY]

40:23.597 --> 40:25.384
GUARD: Davon, it's time.

40:26.268 --> 40:27.660
♪ <i>But when the sun comes up,</i> ♪

40:27.697 --> 40:29.175
♪ <i>the shadows will fall</i> ♪

40:29.212 --> 40:30.389
[INDISTINCT MURMURING]

40:30.426 --> 40:31.613
♪ <i>I'll know I'm enough</i> ♪

40:31.650 --> 40:33.654
♪ <i>to weather the storm</i> ♪

40:34.355 --> 40:36.636
♪ <i>And I may not have a plan, but</i> ♪

40:36.673 --> 40:38.521
♪ <i>I'm still gonna answer</i> ♪

40:38.648 --> 40:42.149
♪ <i>When I get that, I get that call</i> ♪

40:42.329 --> 40:43.893
♪ <i>When I'm feeling way down</i> ♪

40:43.930 --> 40:45.584
♪ <i>under it all</i> ♪

40:46.236 --> 40:47.541
♪ <i>And it gets too heavy</i> ♪

40:47.578 --> 40:49.439
♪ <i>to keep standing tall</i> ♪

40:49.476 --> 40:51.411
♪ <i>Oh, I may be afraid,</i> ♪

40:51.448 --> 40:53.369
♪ <i>but I know I'll find my way</i> ♪

40:53.406 --> 40:54.713
♪ <i>When the sun comes up,</i> ♪

40:54.758 --> 40:56.391
♪ <i>the shadows</i> ♪

40:56.462 --> 40:59.738
♪ <i>The shadows will fall...</i> ♪

41:00.738 --> 41:03.872
VIOLET: <i>And the CCI's
warden awaits word.</i>

41:05.056 --> 41:07.541
<i>Will there be clemency and commutation</i>

41:07.578 --> 41:08.728
<i>from the governor...</i>

41:08.765 --> 41:10.656
♪ <i>The shadows will fall...</i> ♪

41:10.693 --> 41:12.135
<i>...or will the state of Ohio</i>

41:12.172 --> 41:14.039
<i>put an innocent man to death?</i>

41:14.327 --> 41:16.200
♪ <i>At night</i> ♪

41:16.737 --> 41:19.594
♪ <i>When it's hard to sleep</i> ♪

41:19.723 --> 41:21.236
♪ <i>Wondering what's real</i> ♪

41:21.273 --> 41:23.578
♪ <i>and what's just a dream</i> ♪

41:23.615 --> 41:25.103
♪ <i>Breathless and lost</i> ♪

41:25.140 --> 41:27.595
♪ <i>in the in-between</i> ♪

41:27.680 --> 41:30.305
♪ <i>It gets to me, yeah...</i> ♪

41:35.392 --> 41:38.283
- We failed him.
- The system failed him.

41:38.359 --> 41:40.651
We are the system.

41:42.094 --> 41:43.576
At least Daniel Hernandez gets to

41:43.621 --> 41:45.698
walk out of prison a free man.

41:46.484 --> 41:48.351
He's going to law school.

41:48.899 --> 41:51.124
Wants to study criminal law.

41:52.472 --> 41:54.764
There are no acceptable losses.

41:54.917 --> 41:57.072
♪ <i>Oh, I may be afraid</i> ♪

41:57.109 --> 41:58.994
♪ <i>But I know I'll find my way</i> ♪

41:59.031 --> 42:00.346
♪ <i>When the sun comes up,</i> ♪

42:00.383 --> 42:02.080
♪ <i>the shadows</i> ♪

42:02.324 --> 42:04.432
♪ <i>The shadows will fall...</i> ♪

42:05.103 --> 42:08.244
When I was a child,
my parents taught me

42:08.281 --> 42:10.781
that everything happens for a reason.

42:11.325 --> 42:13.312
That there's a bigger plan.

42:13.486 --> 42:16.101
What is meant to be will be.

42:17.126 --> 42:19.095
It's a cruel joke
our parents play on us,

42:19.132 --> 42:21.254
making us believe
that the world is good

42:21.291 --> 42:23.809
and just and kind, because...

42:28.197 --> 42:31.158
...because today, I just can't see it.

42:31.331 --> 42:33.946
What's the plan when an innocent man

42:34.031 --> 42:35.568
loses his life?

